               <p>RICHARD MARKS. I live in Old-street-road; the prisoner was my <rs id="t18280911-391-deflabel2036" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-391-defend2096 t18280911-391-deflabel2036"></join> - I lost two sheets, and a pair of boots, on the 7th of July; my niece, Elizabeth Moorm, brought down the prisoner's bag to me, and I found a number of duplicates in it.</p>
               <p>ELIZABETH MOORM. I lost a pair of stockings and a handkerchief, on the 7th of July; I found the stockings in the prisoner's box in her room, and my handkerchief under her bed - the duplicates were in a blue bag in her box.</p>
